Sentencas: We report an effective method to fabricate long, anode-supported tubular protonic ceramic fuel cells (PCFCs) and test cells in single-cell and short-stack mode.
Titulo: High performance tubular protonic ceramic fuel cells via highly-scalable extrusion process

Sentencas: Further, we use our tubular PCFC platform to directly compare three high performance cathodes reported in literature: BaCo0.4Fe0.4Zr0.1Y0.1O3-delta (BCFZY), Ba0.5Sr0.5Co0.8Fe0.2O3-delta (BSCF), and PrBa0.5-Sr0.5Co1.5Fe0.5O6-delta (PBSCF) using indentical preparation methods, which can minimize effects from variation of materials either due to suppliers or subsequent processing and testing from different research labs.
Titulo: High performance tubular protonic ceramic fuel cells via highly-scalable extrusion process

Sentencas: Using a BCFZY cathode, the maximum power density of our tubular PCFC reaches 164, 308, and 517 mW cm(-2) at 500, 550, and 600 degrees C, respectively.
Titulo: High performance tubular protonic ceramic fuel cells via highly-scalable extrusion process

Sentencas: A 2-cell tubular short stack provides a total power of 2.3 W at 600 degrees C with tube diameters of 0.82 cm and a total tube active length of 3.2 cm.
Titulo: High performance tubular protonic ceramic fuel cells via highly-scalable extrusion process

Sentencas: At 600 degrees C, the maximum power density reaches, 534, 517, and 326 mw cm(-2) for the BSCF, BCFZY, and PBSCF cathodes, respectively.
Titulo: High performance tubular protonic ceramic fuel cells via highly-scalable extrusion process

Sentencas: Under the same conditions, the BSCF-based cell shows the lowest total resistance mostly due to the lowest ohmic resistance and modest polarization resistance.
Titulo: High performance tubular protonic ceramic fuel cells via highly-scalable extrusion process

Sentencas: The BCFZY-based cell has the lowest polarization resistance but larger ohmic resistance leading to a slightly higher total resistance than BSCF.
Titulo: High performance tubular protonic ceramic fuel cells via highly-scalable extrusion process

Sentencas: The PBSCF cell has an ohmic resistance close to BSCF but a total polarization resistance much larger than either BSCF or BCFZY cell which results in the lowest overall performance.
Titulo: High performance tubular protonic ceramic fuel cells via highly-scalable extrusion process
